rComments: Horrid class! For a WGS prof she has much to learn about equity. Made comments in class that were not acceptable and when approached about these comments accused the student of making the comments up! Will never take another class with her!
She is incredibly approachable and very helpful. Instigates critical student discussions, and is very engaging and involved with their ideas. A very fair marker as well. A brilliant professor!

Took both 271 (Pop Culture) and 272 (Queer Cultures) with Dina and had a great experience! The course material (readings) are fantastic, and her slides are detailed enough that you don't really have to take notes. She facilitates and attends to student discussion and questions, however, sometimes lets things drone on for too long. Great courses!

I absolutely love Dina's teaching style and look forward to taking my third course taught by her. She just makes tough concepts easier to understand, and she is easily accessible to talk after class or by email. She's also a pretty fair marker, and as long as you make sense, you're guaranteed to get a good mark.
Great use (and choice!) of video in lecture, pretty understanding when you hand in a late paper too!
She is a phenominal professor with a real passion that is addictive. It is hard to get bored in her class, she gets everyone involved in group discussious and alwaus keeps the class lively!

Awsome class! Extremely entertaining. If you have an undecided free spot for a half credit, Take this course. We watched Crash, Fight Club, Greys Anatomy, Sopranos, Buffy etc. She does an awsome job at allowing students to understand deeper meanings. GREAT COURSE.
Excellent prof. She's energetic fun to have as a prof. and she keeps her way of dressing in sink with popular culture. Never seen her in corduroys or wearing an out-dated suit.

Wow! Dina's Queer Theory course turned out to be everything I'd hoped for. It was challenging, insightful and extremely interesting. It was definately one of the more gruelling theory courses offered....but well worth it. Dina was absolutely brilliant :)

This was my first wmns course and I took it mainly because it sounded easy. Although it did prove to be a good "bird course", i found that I also thoroughly enjoyed every minute of the lectures. I found myself days later to still be pondering ideas brought up in class and this class forced me to think about things i normally don't question/examine.
What can I say about Dina that hasn't been said before? She's a great prof who really cares about her students. Her lectures have always been fantastic.

This has been one of the best courses I have ever taken at Queen's and Dina is main reason I've enjoyed it so much. Her vast knowledge and teaching style is more than anyone can ask for in a prof. I really love everything about her!!!

Dina was the reason I took this course but after hearing her lectures, I am in love with the topic and use/think about the theories a lot. My other professors always comment on how I'm basically molding my academic career after Dina's interests... but it's true, the woman's my hero!
Dina is the kind of prof that makes you believe in yourself and the people around you. She's an intense lecturer but that's part of her charm.

Dina is one of my favourite profs.  She's makes me think of concepts I had never considered, and encourages us to explore our own identities.  She's a remarkable person, and a I think she's a critical component of the Women's Studies Discipline at Queen's.
No Comments
Dina is the BEST! She is such an amazing and incredibly interesting proff that has definately changed my university experience for the better!
An amazing professor....but she shows her bias on topics.... but overall, excellent communicator.

I totally agree about the stuttering! That, combined with the fact that she often read off her notes, really ruined the lectures for me. The material itself is okay, and sometimes her passion for the subject shows through. Hopefully with more teaching experience, those moments will happen more often...
I've loved being in her classes.......can't wait to a chance to take more of her lectures. I've learnt a lot from her.

What can I say? Her stuttering drives me nuts, it makes her seem as if she doesn't know what she is talking about. The constant "um", "er" and "wh..wh.." sounds throughout the lecture just ruin it. If you like analysing absolutely everything, then by all means, take the course!
Very helpful and easy to talk to.  Brings a passion to the topic.  Interesting class.
No Comments
great professor with an honest eagerness to really help students understand the material! to not take one of her courses would be a devastation to your learning!!
Very enjoyable to be in her class.  The time goes fast.
Awesome prof!
Amazing prof!  Inspiring, intelligent and passionate.  Also very stylish. Highly recommended.
